3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20individuals%20that%20were%20sent%20to%20help%20me%20disembark%20this%20plane%20likely%20had%20very%20little%20training%20on%20how%20to%20do%20so%3B%20they%20kept%20having%20to%20place%20the%20chair%20down%20from%20not%20having%20the%20correct%20grip%2C%20and%20they%20were%20holding%20the%20chair%20completely%20sideways%2C%26quot%3B%20Hunter%20wrote%20on%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20never%20informed%20that%20this%20would%20be%20how%20I%20would%20have%20to%20disembark%20the%20plane%2C%20and%20it%20never%20crossed%20my%20mind%20given%20that%20this%20airport%20DOES%20use%20jet%20bridges%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt's%202024%2C%20disabled%20people%20deserve%20a%20more%20dignified%20and%20safe%20way%20to%20fly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20reached%20out%20to%20Hunter%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportation.gov%2Fsites%2Fdot.gov%2Ffiles%2F2023-10%2FSummary%2520Report%25202021.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Transportation%2C%20more%20than%2051%25%20of%20the%2033%2C631%20complaints%20received%20by%20180%20carriers%20in%202021%20%26quot%3Bconcerned%20the%20carriers'%20failure%20to%20provide%20adequate%20assistance%20to%20persons%20using%20wheelchairs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bfocused%20on%20improving%20air%20travel%20for%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20including%20those%20who%20use%20wheelchairs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcx995y8lwlgo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Air%20Canada%20said%20that%20it%20had%20followed%20all%20the%20protocols%20for%20helping%20passengers%20with%20disabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20as%20part%20of%20our%20accessibility%20plan%2C%20we%20will%20be%20reviewing%20airport%20procedures%2C%20including%20for%20smaller%20foreign%20stations%2C%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20working%20with%20local%20airport%20and%20other%20partners%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20provide%20more%20consistent%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20Canada%20did%20not%20immediately%20reply%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20which%20was%20made%20outside%20regular%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20travel%20can%20be%20a%20huge%20source%20of%20anxiety%20for%20wheelchair%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwheelchair-plane-air-travel-vulnerable-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERyan%20Rae%20Harbuck%2C%20who%20has%20been%20paralyzed%20for%20nearly%2027%20years%2C%20wrote%20an%20essay%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%20describing%20what%20it's%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20a%20passenger%20on%20an%20airplane%20when%20you%20are%20a%20wheelchair%20user%20is%20giving%20up%20all%20reigns%20of%20mobility%20and%20independence%2C%26quot%3B%20Harbuck%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20taking%20away%20your%20legs%20and%20expecting%20you%20not%20to%20say%20a%20word%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-blogger-carried-off-air-canada-operated-flight-wheelchair-2024%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716656701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6651aa80a961b37edf39ff41%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-blogger-carried-off-air-canada-operated-flight-wheelchair-2024%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tori%20Hunter%2C%2026%2C%20uses%20an%20electric%20wheelchair%20due%20to%20a%20neuromuscular%20condition%20called%20spinal%20muscular%20atrophy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rrommen%40insider.com%20(Rebecca%20Rommen)%22%2C%